          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-3-1644936704683-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-3-1644936704683-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Whilst everything is in the oven, peel and finely chop (or grate) your <strong>garlic</strong></p><p>Combine the <strong>chopped garlic</strong>, <strong>tomato paste</strong>,<strong> dried oregano</strong>,<strong> 'Nduja </strong>(can't handle the heat? Go easy!) and <strong>half </strong>your <strong>balsamic vinegar </strong>(you'll use the rest later!)<strong> </strong>in a bowl with 1 tbsp <span class=\"text-purple\">[1 1/2 tbsp] </span><span class=\"text-danger\">[2 tbsp]</span> <strong>boiled water</strong></p><p>Season with a pinch of <strong>salt </strong>and give everything a good mix up – this is your <strong>‘Nduja tomato sauce</strong></p>",
      "order": 4,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-4-1644936706868-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-4-1644936706868-x400.jpg",
