            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-5-1644936709759-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Chop <strong>half</strong> your<strong> basil</strong> finely, including the stalks and keep the <strong>remaining basil leaves</strong> whole</p><p>Combine the <strong>chopped basil</strong> in a bowl with your <strong>mayo</strong> and 1 tbsp <span class=\"text-purple\">[1 1/2 tbsp]</span><span class=\"text-danger\"> [2 tbsp]</span> <strong>cold water</strong> – this is your <strong>basil mayo</strong></p><p>Slice your <strong>tomato[es] </strong>into rounds</p><p>Cut your <strong>brioche bun[s]</strong> in half</p>",
      "order": 6,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-6-1644936711795-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-6-1644936711795-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-6-1644936711795-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-6-1644936711795-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-6-1644936711795-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Once the chicken has had an initial 25 min, remove the tray[s] from the oven and spoon your <strong>'Nduja tomato sauce</strong> equally over the top</p><p>Top with the <strong>mozzarella rounds</strong> and return to the oven for 6-7 min or until the mozzarella has melted – this is your <strong>chicken & 'Nduja parmigiana</strong></p><p>Add the <strong>brioche halves</strong> to the other side of the tray[s], cut side up, and put them in the oven for the final 3-4 min or until toasted</p>",
      "order": 7,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-7-1644936714482-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
